Contents of this issue:

Cover - Art by Matt Baker

The Death Dolls - Pencils by Ed Goldfarb, Inks by Robert Baer

The Devil from the Deep -

Ghosts - With a Sense of Humor! - (Text Feature)

An Eye for an Eye

Dream Girl - Pencils by Ed Goldfarb, Inks by Robert Baer

The Pit and the Pendulum - Adapted from Edgar Allen Poe, Pencils and Inks by Everett Raymond Kinstler

Edited by Marion McDermott

This entire issue is a reprint of Nightmare #2 from Ziff-Davis Publishing

The Widow's Lover (6 pages) A former executioner beheads his old boss and is allowed to be his own executioner.

The Tentacles of Death (6 pages) Dr. Mark Savant heads to Genero where the inhabitants are practicing human sacrifice. There he finds a horrible monster called an Octeel.

Text Story- Dr. Osborne's Secret Weapon (2 pages) A future scientist discovers a way to defeat the invading Sirians by disabling atomic energy.

The Bloody Sword (7 pages) Robert MacCloran returns to his ancestral home to claim his birthright, but his evil uncle has other plans.

The Portrait of Death (7 pages) Gregory Harborough finds a painting of himself labelled "Portrait of Death" and is determined to find the artist.

The Finger of Fate (1 page) Dr. Gladys Cross saves the finger of a holyman from being chopped off and gets a reward in return.

Graveyard in the Antarctic (1 page) G. Murray Levick, surgeon with Captain Robert Scott, finds a thousands of dead and dying seals in the Antarctic.

description: The killing of Senator Stanislaw Kane , found dead with his wife and the head of his escort , monopolizes the services of opening news all over the country . However, investigations are carried out hasty to say the least . Among the people who are not convinced by the reconstruction of facts , performed by the police , there is also the popular journalist Eliane Lacombe , who had previously had a relationship with the Senator . Eliane requests Alfa Agency to dig deeper into the life of Kane ... And the survey makes clear that the implications of the affair can trigger a political earthquake ...
name: L'enigma del senatore Kane

description: Collects : Uncanny X-Men (1981) # 487,488 -  Endangered Species  Chapter 6,7,8,9
Collects : Uncanny X-Men (1981) # 489,490 -  Endangered Species  Chapter 10,11,12,13

When Judge Patricia Parker entrusts to the Alfa Agency the investigation into the murder of journalist Jack Hughes , it is clear from the outset that the murderer can only be an assassin by profession . It also begins to emerge the hypothesis that the murder had a link with the disappearance from the body of Hughes of the new CI -4 , an identification microchip inserted under the skin. Nathan manages to track down the killer with an identikit provided by Judge Parker , who also escaped death by a whisker . But other actors are flapping in the background : who is the mysterious Joel Baldwin ? And what relationship ties him to the murder of Hughes and the mysterious "Company " ?
name: Un uomo contro tutti

description: Collects : Uncanny X-Men (1981) # 491 - X-Men (2004) #204 - Endangered Species Chapter 14,15,16,17

Joel Baldwin continues his solitary fight against the "Company ", a little less lonely now that the agent has found in Special Alfa Agent Nathan Never a potential ally. Nathan is to discover how dangerous is the microchip on which he's investigating , the IC -4 . In particular, some models, prototypes that have been illegally modified for experimental purposes and that constantly violate the privacy of their owners . But this is only the beginning , a small experiment on a smaller scale. The goal is total control over people.
name: Controllo totale
